Card
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Physical cards and virtual versions of physical cards.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
In principle, the company is liable for all claims concerning the
issuing and use of the card. In certain situations, the cardholder is
jointly and severally liable for claims regarding use of the card, see
Article 2.21.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
Credit payment
:SKRSLUT.
.br
A credit arrangement can be linked to a Private card account which makes
it possible to pay the balance off in instalments, see Article 7. You can
also agree always to pay the balance in full - and thus avoid interest.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
It is not possible to set up a credit arrangement for a Corporate
card, because companies are always required to pay the full balance
on their accounts when they receive their card invoices. See
Article 2.21 for special liability conditions on Corporate cards.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
